    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear top-tier anchor in **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 83.29 score is fueled by a massive +16% park factor and the premium lead-off spot against R. Nelson. While **Kyle Tucker** (72.71) and **Josh Lowe** (66.40) also serve as primary pillars, **Josh Lowe** is particularly intriguing; despite the lower order placement, his efficiency is buoyed by favorable wind conditions and a strong platoon advantage against W. Warren. We are also capitalizing on the stolen base potential provided by **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.23); his score is significantly elevated by an 85% success rate against a pitcher with a slow delivery, making him a high-leverage start despite facing a tough arm in J. Wrobleski.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the marginal threshold at the MI position, where **Jacob Wilson** (46.86) barely held off **Nasim Nunez** (39.49). While **Nasim Nunez** offers an intriguing profile, he was relegated to the bench primarily due to the daunting matchup against Paul Skenes and an elite opposing catcher whose pop time neutralizes **Nasim Nunez**'s speed-based value. Meanwhile, we continue to monitor the status of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill**, who are unavailable today, and **Jordan Westburg**, who remains sidelined on the IL. We remain cautious regarding **Liam Hicks** (54.36) and **Drake Baldwin** (55.41), whose scores are hovering near the floor; however, they remain in the lineup due to the lack of viable replacements in our current active pool.",
